2020-2021Coaches

Roch Séguin - Head Coach

After completing his high school education, he attended Norwalk CTC (Connecticut, US) and was a member of the JUCO World Series Champion baseball team in 1998.​nce 1999, Roch continued his playing career in the NCBL Div 1 division while gaining experience as a coach at the Midget AAA level in Gatineau, offering private lessons to local youth and also in the Sports Études baseball program in the Outaouais Region. After 3 successful years at the Midget AAA level, he was chosen to coach Team Quebec at the 18U National Championship. In 2014 he was the head coach of the Hull-Volant Junior Élite Baseball program in the U22 LBJEQ. He is also the current president of the Capital City Reds.

Matti Emery - Assistant Coach

A former professional baseball player and manager in Europe (2009-2013, 2 -time Bundesliga All-Star), Head Coach of the Estonian National Baseball Team, Graduate of the University of Bridgeport (NCAA Div. 2) attended on Athletic/Academic scholarship, and former Gee-Gees Captain.  Matti was previously the Head Coach of the Ottawa Gee-Gees, and will be entering his 4th year as Associate Head Coach for Capital City Reds.
